HOUSE BILL No. 1100
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
family law and juvenile law.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 31-9-2-6, AS AMENDED BY P.L.191-2011,
2 SECTION 3, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 6. "Adoptive parent", for purposes of IC 31-19-11,
4 and IC 31-19-17 through IC 31-19-25.5, and IC 31-19-30, means an
5 adult who has become a parent of a child through adoption.
6 SECTION 2. IC 31-19-30 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
7 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
8 JULY 1, 2026]:
9 Chapter 30. Health Insurance Coverage for Adoptive Children
10 Sec. 1. (a) Subject to any requirements under Title IV-E of the
11 Social Security Act (42 U.S.C. 673), if an adoptive child is eligible
12 for coverage:
13 (1) under the Medicaid program; and
14 (2) as a dependent under the adoptive parent's private health
15 insurance;
16 the adoptive parent may opt out of the adoptive child's
17 participation in the Medicaid program.
2026 IN 1100—LS 6212/DI 141

2
1 (b) To opt out of the adoptive child's participation in the
2 Medicaid program, the adoptive parent must file a request with the
3 department.
4 Sec. 2. Before approving an adoptive parent's request under
5 section 1 of this chapter, the department shall ensure that the
6 adoptive child:
7 (1) is eligible for coverage under the adoptive parent's private
8 health insurance; and
9 (2) will not experience a lapse in coverage while changing
10 from Medicaid to private health insurance.
11 Sec. 3. The department shall collaborate with the office of the
12 secretary of family and social services as necessary to administer
13 this chapter.
